description:
&lt;p&gt;Surrey &amp; Sussex Healthcare NHS Trust are seeking to appoint a Specialty Doctor of middle grade level (ST3 level or above) to join our growing GIM/ Short stay team. The post-holders will join the well-established Department of GIM Short stay unit for one year in the first instance with the possibility to extend if mutually agreed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for applicants with experience in acute and/or general internal medicine who also have excellent team-working skills with the abilities and professional skills to work well in a multi-professional team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post would suit doctors who have a keen interest in education and there will be opportunities for simulation training, teaching and quality improvement work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at East Surrey Hospital, the post-holder will be a key senior member of the GIM team with a clear role in ensuring comprehensive care for their inpatients and providing acute assessment on presentation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will join a team of multi-disciplinary staff in providing comprehensive care for their inpatients and emergency admissions. As part of a multidisciplinary team, you will be committed to delivering clinical and quality targets agreed both nationally and locally with the clinical teams and commissioners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is based on the Godstone/ Chaldon short stay unit and its peripheral General Medical Wards under the supervision of the Consultants in Acute and general Medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Doctors who are enthusiastic about working in a strong team of committed physicians to deliver excellent acute care to patients across a variety of clinical settings will be rewarded with a wide and rewarding clinical experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Hanadi Asalieh hanadi.asalieh@nhs.net 01737 768511&lt;/p&gt;
